NDI(R) SDK v6 — vendored build layout (Windows, Linux, macOS)
=============================================================

This directory is the unified NDI_SDK_DIR for grafton-ndi: include/, lib/x64/,
lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/, lib/macOS/.

How to refresh (maintainers)
----------------------------
From a Windows machine with the official v6 installers in one folder (e.g.
``NDI 6 SDK.exe``, ``Install_NDI_SDK_v6_Linux.tar.gz``,
``Install_NDI_SDK_v6_Apple.pkg``), run:

  pwsh -File scripts/vendor-ndi-sdk-from-local.ps1 -SourceDir <path-to-folder>

Linux files are produced via WSL (``yes | sh`` on the Linux installer).
macOS ``libndi.dylib`` is extracted from the Apple .pkg using ``tar`` on Windows.

Distribution and compliance
---------------------------
- Header files: NDI documentation allows including SDK headers in open-source
  distributions; see https://docs.ndi.video/all/developing-with-ndi/sdk/software-distribution
- Libraries: follow the NDI SDK License Agreement supplied with the SDK and
  your product’s obligations for runtime/redistributables and trademarks.
- NDI(R) is a registered trademark of Vizrt NDI AB.

CI does not download the SDK; ``.github/actions/setup-ndi-sdk`` only points
NDI_SDK_DIR here and, on Linux, recreates ``libndi.so`` symlinks for the linker.
